event.title: was named by F.X. Schreiner in 1893

data.event: Originally a mining camp, Cumberland was named by F.X. Schreiner in 1893 after the Cumberland coal region of the Appalachian Mountains.

event.title: gained a post office on October 13, 1894

data.event: Cumberland gained a post office on October 13, 1894.

event.title: Today, the Enumclaw post office serves

data.event: Today, the Enumclaw post office serves this area.

event.title: 1989 the county-wide transit and sewage waste municipality known

data.event: In 1989 the county-wide transit and sewage waste municipality known as "Metro" (short for Metropolitan King County), planned a 25-year sewage sludge waste spraying on the 400 acres (1.6 km2) of pristine woods northwest of the town.
The EIS showed a number of toxins present in the sludge, and the project was officially cancelled in 1992.
